 \"to\": 6754}, {\"ngram\": \"God\", \"from\": 6763, \"to\": 6766}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A Duke Divinity student prayed in chapel, Strange one, fabulous one, fluid and ever becoming, do not allow us to make our ideas of you into an idol.\", \"from\": 6769, \"to\": 6918, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6771, \"end\": 6775, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duke\", \"score\": 0.765480341845029, \"rank\": 0.30636927581500384, \"text\": \"Duke\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duke\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duke\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"chapel\", \"from\": 6803, \"to\": 6809}, {\"ngram\": \"Strange one\", \"from\": 6811, \"to\": 6822}, {\"ngram\": \"fluid\", \"from\": 6838, \"to\": 6843}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 6876, \"to\": 6878}, {\"ngram\": \"our ideas\", \"from\": 6887, \"to\": 6896}, {\"ngram\": \"an idol\", \"from\": 6909, \"to\": 6916}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You are as close to us as our own breath and yet your essence transcends all that we can imagine.\", \"from\": 6919, \"to\": 7016, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 6939, \"to\": 6941}, {\"ngram\": \"our own breath\", \"from\": 6945, \"to\": 6959}, {\"ngram\": \"your essence\", \"from\": 6968, \"to\": 6980}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You are mother, father, and parent.\", \"from\": 7017, \"to\": 7052, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"mother\", \"from\": 7025, \"to\": 7031}, {\"ngram\": \"father\", \"from\": 7033, \"to\": 7039}, {\"ngram\": \"parent\", \"from\": 7045, \"to\": 7051}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You are sister, brother, and sibling.\", \"from\": 7053, \"to\": 7090, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sister\", \"from\": 7061, \"to\": 7067}, {\"ngram\": \"brother\", \"from\": 7069, \"to\": 7076}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You are drag queen, and trans man, and gender fluid, incapable of limiting your vast expressions of beauty, embodied in us, your creation.\", \"from\": 7091, \"to\": 7229, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"your vast expressions\", \"from\": 7166, \"to\": 7187}, {\"ngram\": \"beauty\", \"from\": 7191, \"to\": 7197}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 7211, \"to\": 7213}, {\"ngram\": \"your creation\", \"from\": 7215, \"to\": 7228}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We recognize flesh, in all its forms, is made holy in you.\", \"from\": 7230, \"to\": 7288, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"flesh\", \"from\": 7243, \"to\": 7248}, {\"ngram\": \"all its forms\", \"from\": 7253, \"to\": 7266}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With thanksgiving, we celebrate your manifestation in all its glorious forms.\", \"from\": 7289, \"to\": 7366, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"thanksgiving\", \"from\": 7294, \"to\": 7306}, {\"ngram\": \"your manifestation\", \"from\": 7321, \"to\": 7339}, {\"ngram\": \"all its glorious forms\", \"from\": 7343, \"to\": 7365}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Blessed are our bodies, blessed is our love, blessed are we when we celebrate that which the world turns away.\", \"from\": 7367, \"to\": 7477, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"our bodies\", \"from\": 7379, \"to\": 7389}, {\"ngram\": \"our love\", \"from\": 7402, \"to\": 7410}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 7456, \"to\": 7465}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fill our hearts with a pride rooted in resistance to all that seeks to destroy.\", \"from\": 7478, \"to\": 7557, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"our hearts\", \"from\": 7483, \"to\": 7493}, {\"ngram\": \"a pride\", \"from\": 7499, \"to\": 7506}, {\"ngram\": \"resistance\", \"from\": 7517, \"to\": 7527}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"[4] These two definitions are in direct contradiction to each other.\", \"from\": 7557, \"to\": 7627, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"These two definitions\", \"from\": 7562, \"to\": 7583}, {\"ngram\": \"direct contradiction\", \"from\": 7591, \"to\": 7611}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Oddly, the new religion works backwards from how most religions emerge, at least in how I understand the history of religion.\", \"from\": 7631, \"to\": 7756, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the new religion\", \"from\": 7638, \"to\": 7654}, {\"ngram\": \"most religions\", \"from\": 7680, \"to\": 7694}, {\"ngram\": \"the history\", \"from\": 7732, \"to\": 7743}, {\"ngram\": \"religion\", \"from\": 7747, \"to\": 7755}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In most religions, a deity is discovered and worshipped and only then do the practices and proscriptions of the religion come into view.\", \"from\": 7757, \"to\": 7893, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"most religions\", \"from\": 7760, \"to\": 7774}, {\"ngram\": \"a deity\", \"from\": 7776, \"to\": 7783}, {\"ngram\": \"the practices\", \"from\": 7830, \"to\": 7843}, {\"ngram\": \"proscriptions\", \"from\": 7848, \"to\": 7861}, {\"ngram\": \"the religion\", \"from\": 7865, \"to\": 7877}, {\"ngram\": \"view\", \"from\": 7888, \"to\": 7892}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Think of how Judaism emerged.\", \"from\": 7894, \"to\": 7923, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7907, \"end\": 7914, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judaism\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2017609758069751e-13, \"text\": \"Judaism\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judaism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judaism\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"God called Abram.\", \"from\": 7924, \"to\": 7941, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"God\", \"from\": 7924, \"to\": 7927}, {\"ngram\": \"Abram\", \"from\": 7935, \"to\": 7940}]}, {\"sentence\": \"God called Moses.\", \"from\": 7942, \"to\": 7959, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"God\", \"from\": 7942, \"to\": 7945}, {\"ngram\": \"Moses\", \"from\": 7953, \"to\": 7958}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Moses led the people out of slavery.\", \"from\": 7960, \"to\": 7996, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Moses\", \"from\": 7960, \"to\": 7965}, {\"ngram\": \"the people\", \"from\": 7970, \"to\": 7980}, {\"ngram\": \"slavery\", \"from\": 7988, \"to\": 7995}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was onlyafterGod revealed himself that he gave the the Law.\", \"from\": 7997, \"to\": 8059, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the the Law\", \"from\": 8047, \"to\": 8058}]}, {\"sentence\": \"God self-reveals first.\", \"from\": 8060, \"to\": 8083, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"God\", \"from\": 8060, \"to\": 8063}]}, {\"sentence\": \"God commands second.\", \"from\": 8084, \"to\": 8104, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"God\", \"from\": 8084, \"to\": 8087}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Not so with this yet-unnamed religion.\", \"from\": 8106, \"to\": 8144, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this yet-unnamed religion\", \"from\": 8118, \"to\": 8143}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The practice is first.\", \"from\": 8145, \"to\": 8167, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The practice\", \"from\": 8145, \"to\": 8157}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The practice is the celebration of the ugly, the inclusion of the bizarre, the celebration of the garish.\", \"from\": 8168, \"to\": 8273, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The practice\", \"from\": 8168, \"to\": 8180}, {\"ngram\": \"the celebration\", \"from\": 8184, \"to\": 8199}, {\"ngram\": \"the inclusion\", \"from\": 8213, \"to\": 8226}, {\"ngram\": \"the celebration\", \"from\": 8243, \"to\": 8258}, {\"ngram\": \"the garish\", \"from\": 8262, \"to\": 8272}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bodies are irrelevant and fluid.\", \"from\": 8274, \"to\": 8306, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Bodies\", \"from\": 8274, \"to\": 8280}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sexuality is central.\", \"from\": 8307, \"to\": 8328, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Sexuality\", \"from\": 8307, \"to\": 8316}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Repressed sexuality is verboten.\", \"from\": 8329, \"to\": 8361, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Repressed sexuality\", \"from\": 8329, \"to\": 8348}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The only sin is exclusion and lack of diversity.\", \"from\": 8362, \"to\": 8410, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The only sin\", \"from\": 8362, \"to\": 8374}, {\"ngram\": \"exclusion\", \"from\": 8378, \"to\": 8387}, {\"ngram\": \"lack\", \"from\": 8392, \"to\": 8396}, {\"ngram\": \"diversity\", \"from\": 8400, \"to\": 8409}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Only the unenlightened are shocked and embarrassed.\", \"from\": 8411, \"to\": 8462, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This new religion tolerates no intolerance, and still persecutes anyone who dares disagree with its tenants.\", \"from\": 8463, \"to\": 8571, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This new religion\", \"from\": 8463, \"to\": 8480}, {\"ngram\": \"no intolerance\", \"from\": 8491, \"to\": 8505}, {\"ngram\": \"anyone\", \"from\": 8528, \"to\": 8534}, {\"ngram\": \"its tenants\", \"from\": 8559, \"to\": 8570}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Watch what has happened to Christian theologians who have dared disagree with the LGBTQ+ movement in mainline seminaries.\", \"from\": 8572, \"to\": 8693, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8599, \"end\": 8620, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_theology\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Christian theologians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_theology\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_theology\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the LGBTQ+ movement\", \"from\": 8650, \"to\": 8669}, {\"ngram\": \"mainline seminaries\", \"from\": 8673, \"to\": 8692}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The only thing left is to find a deity who will meet their needs.\", \"from\": 8695, \"to\": 8760, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The only thing\", \"from\": 8695, \"to\": 8709}, {\"ngram\": \"a deity\", \"from\": 8726, \"to\": 8733}, {\"ngram\": \"their needs\", \"from\": 8748, \"to\": 8759}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It cannot be YWHW or a of god of any monotheistic religion, not without cognitive dissonance anyway.\", \"from\": 8761, \"to\": 8861, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"god\", \"from\": 8787, \"to\": 8790}, {\"ngram\": \"any monotheistic religion\", \"from\": 8794, \"to\": 8819}, {\"ngram\": \"cognitive dissonance\", \"from\": 8833, \"to\": 8853}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even Dionysos is not particularly promising.\", \"from\": 8862, \"to\": 8906, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Even Dionysos\", \"from\": 8862, \"to\": 8875}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I suspect the evangelists of this new religion will simply use the name god and redefine it so thoroughly as to render it useless.\", \"from\": 8907, \"to\": 9037, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the evangelists\", \"from\": 8917, \"to\": 8932}, {\"ngram\": \"this new religion\", \"from\": 8936, \"to\": 8953}, {\"ngram\": \"the name\", \"from\": 8970, \"to\": 8978}, {\"ngram\": \"god\", \"from\": 8979, \"to\": 8982}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Also By Layne Wallace [1]https://www.orwellfoundation.com/the-orwell-foundation/orwell/essays-and-other-works/notes-on-nationalism/ [2]https://www.worldhistory.org/Bacchus/#:~:text=Definition&text=Bacchus%20was%20the%20god%20of,god%20of%20wine%20Liber%20Pater.\", \"from\": 9049, \"to\": 9313, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9057, \"end\": 9062, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Layne_Staley\", \"score\": 0.9999999988212949, \"rank\": 1.1785411786437847e-09, \"text\": \"Layne\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Layne_Staley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Layne_Staley\"}, {\"begin\": 9063, \"end\": 9070, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alfred_Russel_Wallace\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.912219939314917e-17, \"text\": \"Wallace\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alfred_Russel